k\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dhe1665702749084.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dhe1665702749084.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dhe1665702749084.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dhe1665702749084\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__context_w1564ab1b5b1_w1565ab1b5_w1566ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__p_d67514e1_d67515e1_d67516e1\">When installing the RMS License Manager, an uninstall\n            script is created. If you used the default location, this can be found in:\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">C:/Program Files (x86)/Common Files/SafeNetSentinel/Uninstall</span>. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__p_d67517e1_d67518e1_d67519e1\">When uninstalling, you will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine. This allows you to move your RMS License Manager to a different machine and reuse the license. This feature is also useful if you wish to change from a cloud-served license to a license file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__p_d67520e1_d67521e1_d67522e1\">To uninstall:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__li_d30227e1_d30228e1_d30229e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run the <span class=\"ph filepath\">uninstallrms.bat</span> script and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> in the subsequent dialog box.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__li_d30230e1_d30231e1_d30232e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">At the first prompt, press <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Enter</span> to continue with the uninstall.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__li_d30233e1_d30234e1_d30235e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If a cloud-served license is detected, you are asked if you want to reconfigure your proxy settings, and to enter the Entitlement ID of the license you are returning.\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__li_d30236e1_d30237e1_d30238e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__p_d67523e1_d67524e1_d67525e1\">Select yes (<code class=\"ph codeph\">Y</code>) to re-enter the proxy details, or no (<code class=\"ph codeph\">N</code>) to continue with your existing proxy settings.\n You will need an internet connection for this process.</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__li_d30239e1_d30240e1_d30241e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Enter the Entitlement ID for the cloud-served license you are returning. Press <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Enter</span> to continue.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__li_d30242e1_d30243e1_d30244e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally enter an additional Entitlement ID to return another license, or press <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Enter</span> to continue. You can return multiple Entitlement IDs.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__li_d30245e1_d30246e1_d30247e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">If a license file is detected, you are warned that the license file will be deleted. You can quit the process to make a copy of the file before continuing. Alternatively, you can download a new license file from the Sentinel EMS Customer Portal.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"dhe1665702749084__li_d30248e1_d30249e1_d30250e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">The uninstall script will now proceed to clean up the RMS License Manager and Cloud Plug-in (if applicable), and return the license.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uninstalling Sentinel RMS License Manager on Windows When installing the RMS License Manager, an uninstall script is created. If you used the default location, this can be found in: C:/Program Files (x86)/Common Files/SafeNetSentinel/Uninstall . When uninstalling, you will be asked to return your license so that you can use it on a different machine. This allows you to move your RMS License Manager to a different machine and reuse the license. This feature is also useful if you wish to change from a cloud-served license to a license file. To uninstall: Run the uninstallrms.bat script and click OK in the subsequent dialog box. At the first prompt, press Enter to continue with the uninstall. If a cloud-served license is detected, you are asked if you want to reconfigure your proxy settings, and to enter the Entitlement ID of the license you are returning. Select yes ( Y ) to re-enter the proxy details, or no ( N ) to continue with your existing proxy settings. You will need an internet connection for this process. Enter the Entitlement ID for the cloud-served license you are returning. Press Enter to continue. Optionally enter an additional Entitlement ID to return another license, or press Enter to continue. You can return multiple Entitlement IDs. If a license file is detected, you are warned that the license file will be deleted. You can quit the process to make a copy of the file before continuing. Alternatively, you can download a new license file from the Sentinel EMS Customer Portal. The uninstall script will now proceed to clean up the RMS License Manager and Cloud Plug-in (if applicable), and return the license. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}